oxcarbazepine.statement:
This drug and its active metabolite (10-monohydroxy derivative, MHD) cross the human placenta. Oxcarbazepine is (structurally) closely related to carbamazepine, which is considered to be teratogenic in humans. This drug is teratogenic in rats.  The risk of having an abnormal child as a result of antiepileptic medication is far outweighed by the dangers to the mother and fetus of uncontrolled epilepsy. 
